a.persistence-api is an API-only artifact; its resolved POM only adds jakarta.annotation-api transitively, and meaningful coverage can be reached by exercising annotations, API defaults, exceptions, Persistence bootstrap behavior, and SPI with local test doubles rather than a real provider or database.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Generated tests should avoid depending on a real JPA provider unless explicitly testing provider integration; local PersistenceProviderResolver/PersistenceProvider stubs are sufficient. For 4.0.0-M5, update Query and TypedQuery test doubles to implement the new setParameters(Object...) API.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"End-to-end persistence with a real EntityManager would require an implementation such as Hibernate or EclipseLink and likely JDBC/database setup, but that is not necessary for API reachability coverage and would broaden the test scope.\",\n    \"Because the compile failure is caused by new abstract API methods, stale hand-written stubs may fail javac even though no extra dependency or Docker setup is missing.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c84d9aee973426c016a3e7908bfe48193a3f673dfc52e381c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3274, "output": 741, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22959, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782479102770, "responseId": "resp_0c84d9aee973426c016a3e78ff54088193a09804390cf8d73f"}}
